This tree is definitely starting to lose its leaves faster, even though I can't really tell from whats on the ground. The leaves that are still on the tree are fraile, and crispy. Majority of the leaves are half green, half brown and curled up. There are still some green leaves but those are starting to turn as well. The trunk of the tree is starting to look grey and dry.

The tree is still looking fairly green. The leaves that are turning are more yellow than brown. Leaves look healthy but are starting to get to the point where they might end up turning brown.  I've noticed that the trunk is peeling a little and starting to turn into a lighter color. I also noticed the leaves having white specs on them.
I am still surprised that this tree has had almost no significant changes for the past few weeks. The weather was like a roller coaster from wind to cold and rain.
The tree has a lot of fallen leaves on the ground. Which was a big change from the past few weeks.
